summary: 'Avengers: Endgame' Has More Spoilers Than 'Infinity War,' Director Says
title: 'Avengers: Endgame' Has More Spoilers Than 'Infinity War,' Director Says
excerpt: "The smallest clue in a trailer can ruin a movie," says co-director Joe Russo.
description:
…Russo asserted that it is important for fans to protect themselves from spoilers: “I encourage people to go opening weekend because I’m sure everything is going to hit the internet the moment the movie hits the screen.”

He continued: “There’s a culture that monetizes secrets around these films — an online culture, a media culture. That’s fair, but it’s also fair for the filmmaker to protect the story.” That, it turns out, is why the Endgame promotion has limited as much information about the movie as it has.

The Russos asking us to trust them and go in blind after they caused so many of us to have a severe emotional response to Infinity War without any warning because it would have been a “story spoiler” is absolutely ridiculous and the height of pure egotism. The story of Infinity War wasn’t even that good, dude. You relied on shock value for $$ and you’re probably doing it again. 

…this annoyed me. I hate being a puppet on a string for Marvel.
